						<summary>

						<p>The inscription seems to be engraved in characters of about the 10th-11th century A.D. It records an endowment of a hundred <hi rend="italic">kāśu</hi> raised by donation by Śaṅkaraṉ Nīlakaṇṭaṉ a native of Śēndanūr in the Pāṇḍya country, for feeding some devotees in the temple (at Iṟaiyānaraiyūr ?) on the day of Jyēshṭhā in Dhanus month every year.</p>						

						</summary>
